== Access == * Railway ({{ill|JR East|ja|JR東日本|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/JR East|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 東日本旅客鉄道}}) : Approximately 40 minutes by {{ill|Seibu Sightseeing Bus|ja|西武観光バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seibu Sightseeing Bus|qq=}} from [[:en:Manza-Kazawaguchi Station|Manza-Kashizawa-guchi Station]] on the [[:en:Agatsuma Line|Agatsuma Line]]. : Approximately 90 minutes by Seibu Sightseeing Bus (via Manza-Kashizawa-guchi Station) from [[:en:Karuizawa Station|Karuizawa Station]] on the [[:en:Hokuriku Shinkansen|Hokuriku Shinkansen]]. * There are three bus stops in the Manza Onsen area: "Manza Onsen" (near the entrance), the central "Manza Prince Hotel" bus stop, and the "Manza Onsen Ue" bus stop. * Automobile: : The only road available year‑round is the paid {{ill|Manza Highway|ja|万座ハイウェー|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Manza Highway|qq=}}, about 22 km from Mihara in Tsumagoi Village. : From spring to autumn, [[:en:Japan National Route 292|National Route 292]] (Shiga‑Kusatsu Kogen Route) is available (it is closed in winter). Note that due to the eruption alert level for [[:en:Mount Kusatsu-Shirane|Kusatsu Shirane]], the section between the (Kusatsu) {{ill|Sesshōgahara|ja|殺生河原|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sesshōgahara|qq=}} parking area and the Manza Sansaji intersection may be closed. As of April 2019, the eruption alert level is 2; although normally it would be closed all day, an exception allows passage during daytime only (bicycles, motorcycles, and convertibles are not permitted; weather conditions such as fog may also cause closures).
